        These show that Python lists and tuples behave as
        described above::

            sage: [i for i in EclObject([1,2,3])]
            [<ECL: 1>, <ECL: 2>, <ECL: 3>]
            sage: [i for i in EclObject((1,2,3))]
            [<ECL: 1>, <ECL: 2>, <ECL: 3>]

